name: Food Matters I (formerly NEW101Y1)
description: Exploring key themes and different kinds of knowledge implied by the notion of "learning without borders", this interdisciplinary course looks at food as a system that impacts every element of life.  It makes connections with other New One topics, links students' own food choices to global forces, and considers what global citizenship might mean in the context of food.
exclusions: INI, Munk, SMC, TRN, UNI, VIC, and WDW One; NEW101Y1/NEW102Y1/NEW103Y1/NEW104Y1
